ts of the effectiveness of pro-poor tourism as a development strategy and tackles the issue of who benefits from tourism’s potential role in poverty reduction. This timely book therefore makes a major contribution to the ongoing debate about tourism’s role in economic development, postcolonial politics, and North-South relations at a time when international trade negotiations appear poised to further open up developing countries to international tourism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aPovertyxEntwicklungsländer. 0aPoverty. 0aTourism. 4aTourism industry. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Hospitality, Travel & Tourism.2bisacsh  aNorth-South relations.  adestination development.  aeconomic development.  apostcolonial politics.  apoverty alleviation.  apro-poor tourism.  asustainable development.1 aBrent Ritchie, J. R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChok, Stephanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodwin, Harold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, C. Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, C. Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHarrison, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacbeth, Jim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScheyvens, Regina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchilcher, Daniela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchipani, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpenceley, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWarren, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/